<h2>Model Constraints</h2>

<p>The constraints in this section apply to models. What constitutes
the from-model and to-model depends on which liquid helpers you're
using.</p>

<ul>
  <li><code>\{{liquid-outlet}}</code> matches against the actual
  router-provided models before and after the transition.</li>
  <li><code>\{{#liquid-with}}</code> and <code>\{{liquid-bind}}</code>
    match against their own bound contexts.</li>
  <li><code>\{{#liquid-if}}</code> matches against its predicate.</li>
</ul>

<p>These are the three model constraint methods:</p>

<dl class="dl-horizontal">
  <dt>fromModel</dt>
  <dd>Matches the model before the transition.</dd>
  <dt>toModel</dt>
  <dd>Matches the model after the transition.</dd>
  <dt>betweenModels</dt>
  <dd>Matches the model both before and after the transition.</dd>
</dl>

